Hard drive Installation
-----------------------

How do I install Troubleshooter on my hard drive?

Easy!

Create a directory on your hard drive called 'Troubleshooter' or something
like that and insert this disk.

Double-click on the disk icon, and drag the "TShooter" icon over to the new
directory on your hard drive.



Special page numbers in the program
-----------------------------------

P100 - Main Index (the screen which is displayed at the start)

P175 - Test page (allows you to test printers, disk drive, sound and picture)

P199 - Quit (Quits)



